# UI design tokens rule (this session)

Any new UI element **must only use** the design tokens listed below. Do **not** hardcode arbitrary values (e.g. `p-[13px]`, `rounded-[11px]`, `text-[#abc]`). If a design requires a value that does not exist in the token list, **flag it to the user first** and suggest adding it to `app/globals.css` or this rule, rather than using a bracket/magic number.

---

## Source of truth

- **Theme:** `app/globals.css` — `:root` and `@theme inline` (Tailwind v4, no tailwind.config).
- **Reference usage:** `components/` (Footer, LanguageSwitcher, Logo, MatchChatWindow, MatchCongratulationsModal) and existing app pages.

---

## Colors (use only these)

**Brand (from globals.css):**
- `matcher`, `matcher-dark`, `matcher-bright`, `matcher-teal`, `matcher-amber`, `matcher-coral`, `matcher-mint`, `matcher-pale`
- `charcoal` (dark mode / premium depth, e.g. `text-charcoal`, `bg-charcoal`)
- Opacity variants allowed: e.g. `matcher/15`, `matcher/30`, `matcher-pale/30`, `matcher-pale/50`, `bg-matcher-dark`

**Neutrals (Tailwind grays used in project):**
- `white`, `black`
- `gray-50`, `gray-100`, `gray-200`, `gray-300`, `gray-400`, `gray-500`, `gray-600`, `gray-700`, `gray-900`
- Overlays: `black/40`, `black/60`, `white/15`, `white/20`

**Semantic (from globals.css):**
- `background`, `foreground`, `primary`, `muted-foreground`

**Accent (used in demos only):**
- `rose-400`, `rose-500`, `red-500` (swipe demo) — prefer matcher palette for new UI.

Do **not** use raw hex in class names (e.g. `bg-[#a5c044]`). Use the token name (e.g. `bg-matcher`).

